<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 15:09:24 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Rotterdam museum buys Van Gogh after displaying it for 40 years</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/rotterdam-museum-buys-van-gogh-after-displaying-it-for-40-years/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232336 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-art-and-culture category-society category-van-gogh"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Rotterdam museum buys Van Gogh after displaying it for 40 years</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T15:07:18+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-232338" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_232338"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1080" sizes="(max-width: 1390px) 100vw, 1390px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/528783-Van-Gogh-Stilleven-met-aardappels-foto-Studio-Tromp-f7e8af-original-1709626323.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/528783-Van-Gogh-Stilleven-met-aardappels-foto-Studio-Tromp-f7e8af-original-1709626323.jpg 1390w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/528783-Van-Gogh-Stilleven-met-aardappels-foto-Studio-Tromp-f7e8af-original-1709626323-560x435.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/528783-Van-Gogh-Stilleven-met-aardappels-foto-Studio-Tromp-f7e8af-original-1709626323-1200x932.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/528783-Van-Gogh-Stilleven-met-aardappels-foto-Studio-Tromp-f7e8af-original-1709626323-768x597.jpg 768w" width="1390"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-232338"> Collectie Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen, Rotterdam</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Rotterdam’s Boijmans van Beuningen museum has bought a painting by Vincent van Gogh that has been hanging in its galleries for 40 years.</p><p>The museum said it had acquired the work, <em>Still Life with Potatoes</em>, which dates from 1887, for an undisclosed sum to ensure it stayed in the Netherlands. It was previously on long-term loan from a private collection.</p><p>“The risk with a long-term loan, especially with famous artists like Vincent van Gogh, is that the work can be recalled or sold, possibly abroad,” <a href="https://boijmans.pr.co/nl-NL/235381-onder-embargo-museum-boijmans-van-beuningen-koopt-vincent-van-goghs-stilleven-met-aardappels-">the museum said in a press release</a>. “This purchase ensures that this Van Gogh will stay in the Netherlands’ national collection.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Numerous backers, including Vereniging Rembrandt, Stichting Boijmans van Beuningen and VriendenLoterij, as well as private investors, contributed to the purchase fund, the museum said.</p><p>Van Gogh painted the work in Paris, shortly after finishing a short spell at art school in Antwerp, using a much wider colour palette than in his later, better-known work The Potato Eaters.</p><p>He wrote to his brother Theo that he wanted to portray the exact texture and irregular shape of the potatoes in his still life.</p><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-232340" class="wp-caption alignnone" id="attachment_232340" style="width: 420px"><noscript><img alt="" class="size-medium wp-image-232340" decoding="async" height="560" sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-420x560.jpeg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-420x560.jpeg 420w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-901x1200.jpeg 901w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-768x1023.jpeg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-1153x1536.jpeg 1153w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551.jpeg 1501w" width="420"/></noscript><img alt="" class="lazyload size-medium wp-image-232340" data-sizes="(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px" data-src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-420x560.jpeg" data-srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-420x560.jpeg 420w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-901x1200.jpeg 901w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-768x1023.jpeg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551-1153x1536.jpeg 1153w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Wikipedia_Vincent_van_Gogh_-_Head_of_an_Old_Peasant_Woman_with_White_Cap_-_F146_JH551.jpeg 1501w" decoding="async" height="560" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22%20viewBox=%220%200%20420%20560%22%3E%3C/svg%3E" width="420"/><figcaption class="wp-caption-text" id="caption-attachment-232340">Head of an Old Farmer’s Wife With a White Hat. Wikipedia</figcaption></figure><p>Another Van Gogh work, Head of an Old Farmer’s Wife in a White Hat, fetched €4.5 million at the Tefaf art fair in Maastricht at the weekend.</p><p>The portrait, measuring 63cm by 48cm, is believed to have been painted in 1884, when Van Gogh was working in Nuenen, Brabant. It was acquired from the M.S. Rau gallery in the United States by an unnamed private buyer who owns a museum outside Europe.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/art-and-culture/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/van-gogh/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232336</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 15:07:18 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Five teenagers arrested at Antwerp port, hunting for cocaine</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/five-teenagers-arrested-at-antwerp-port-hunting-for-cocaine/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232337 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-crime category-drugs"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Five teenagers arrested at Antwerp port, hunting for cocaine</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T15:03:08+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-229990" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_229990"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="677" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_673587450_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_673587450_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_673587450_S-560x379.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Depositphotos_673587450_S-768x520.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-229990"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Five Dutch teenagers have been arrested on Antwerp port premises where they were thought to be looking for a consignment of cocaine.</p><p>Three of the five, aged 14, 17 and 18, were picked up on the night of March 7 after port police received warning that three suspicious people had been spotted. The two others, aged 14 and 19, were arrested at the same location on Sunday night.</p><p>According to the AD, a quantity of cocaine was also found, but the paper did not say where or how much.</p><p>In January, police at Rotterdam port found two 14-year olds among different gangs of drugs runners waiting to remove drugs from a container. Antwerp and Rotterdam ports are considered to be the main gateway for bringing cocaine into Europe.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/drugs/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232337</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 15:03:08 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Rangers want to use klaxons and firecrackers to scare off wolves</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/rangers-want-to-use-klaxons-and-firecrackers-to-scare-off-wolves/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232327 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-society category-wolf newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Rangers want to use klaxons and firecrackers to scare off wolves</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T14:14:37+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-159298" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_159298"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="681" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf-560x381.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf-768x523.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf-640x436.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/wolf-130x89.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-159298"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Forest rangers in Drenthe and Friesland are planning to use klaxons and firecrackers to scare off a wolf that has become too accustomed to humans.</p><p>The young wolf has been seen approaching people in a nature reserve that spans the two provinces. Rangers believe the animal may have lost its fear of humans after being offered food.</p><p>It is not the first time nature wardens have resorted to unusual measures to deter wolves. In January Gelderland province <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/01/province-can-use-paintball-guns-to-scare-off-wolves-court-rules/">won the latest stage of a long-running legal battle</a> to be allowed to use paintball pellets to stop the animals getting too close to humans.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Nature conservation Faunaberscherming, which brought the case, has threatened further legal action if Gelderland province allows rangers to use paintball guns against wolves, arguing it would breach European Union rules.</p><p>Shepherds in the Veluwe region have been given gas horns to use against wolves, but it is unclear if the devices have had any effect.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/wolf/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232327</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 14:14:37 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Eneco brings in fees for solar panel owners who feed back power</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/eneco-brings-in-fees-for-solar-panel-owners-who-feed-back-power/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232329 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-energy category-energy-contracts"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Eneco brings in fees for solar panel owners who feed back power</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T14:08:26+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-206589" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_206589"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-640x480.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/IMG_17881-130x98.jpg 130w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-206589"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Eneco has become the latest Dutch electricity company to introduce fees for solar panel owners who feed power they have produced but not used back into the grid.</p><p>The charges will apply to all new customers and to current customers with a variable contract, the <a href="https://news.eneco.com/eneco-will-redistribute-costs-of-fed-in-energy/">company said on Monday</a>. The exact fees per kWh have yet to be calculated and until that is done in the summer, solar panel owners will pay €6 a month in additional fees.</p><p>The company said it will charge customers as long as the current mechanism for feeding electricity into the grid continues. Solar panel owners are able to deduct the electricity they produce but don’t use from their regular bills.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The government had wanted to scrap the system and replace it by payments but the senate voted against that plan last month.</p><p>Most Dutch energy firms have now introduced some sort of fee for solar panel owners and Essent and Vattenfall have also said they are considering doing so.</p><p>Meanwhile, national grid operator Tennet says it needs €160 billion over the next 10 years to improve and upgrade the main network and provide connections for several major wind energy projects.</p><p>The state-owned company booked net profit of €1.8 billion last year, a 50% rise on 2022, but says the shortage of grid capacity remains a major problem.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/energy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/energy-contracts/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232329</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 14:08:26 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Activists who targeted Vermeer painting in The Hague win appeal</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/activists-who-targeted-vermeer-painting-in-the-hague-win-appeal/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232323 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-art-and-culture category-court-cases category-vermeer newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Activists who targeted Vermeer painting in The Hague win appeal</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T13:39:48+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-205453" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_205453"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="429" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screenshot-2022-10-27-at-15.25.10.png" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screenshot-2022-10-27-at-15.25.10.png 600w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screenshot-2022-10-27-at-15.25.10-560x400.png 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screenshot-2022-10-27-at-15.25.10-87x62.png 87w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Screenshot-2022-10-27-at-15.25.10-130x93.png 130w" width="600"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-205453"> A still from a video of the protest 
taken by another museum visitor</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Three protestors who threw liquid at Johannes Vermeer’s Girl with a Pearl Earring and glued themselves to the wall have had their sentences overturned on appeal.</p><p>The Belgian activists from the group Just Stop Oil targeted the painting in the Mauritshuis museum in The Hague in October 2022 to raise awareness of climate change.</p><p>The painting itself, which dates from around 1665, was undamaged, but the frame and the protective glass needed to be cleaned. The museum had to compensate visitors who were unable to see the artwork while it was removed.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>One of the three men threw the liquid while the other glued himself to the wall and the third filmed the scene.</p><p>District court judges sentenced the men to a two-month spell in prison, half of it suspended. But the appeal court said a jail term would infringe their right to freedom of expression and deter other people who wanted to protest peacefully.</p><p>The court also gave the men credit for inspecting the painting beforehand to make sure the canvas would not be damaged by their actions.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/art-and-culture/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/court-cases/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/vermeer/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232323</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 13:39:48 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Shortage of trained police holding back cybercrime detection</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/lack-of-police-training-holding-back-cybercrime-detection-rate/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232316 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-crime category-tech"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Shortage of trained police holding back cybercrime detection</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T11:08:02+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-232317" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_232317"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1335" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L-1200x801.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L-768x513.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_342541304_L-1536x1025.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-232317"> Digital and online offences, such as fraud, account for around 5% of complaints. Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Just one in 10 cases of online crime leads to the identification of a suspect, a report by the Dutch government’s data research bureau WODC has found.</p><p>Police are hampered by a shortage of trained experts and a general lack of awareness of the severity of online crime. Victims are also less likely to come forward than those affected by other forms of crime.</p><p>Cybercrime, such as hacking or using ransomware, accounted for just 1% of a sample of 300,000 reported offences, while digital crime, which covers the use of online technology in more general offences such as fraud and making threats, made up 4%.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>WODC <a href="https://www.wodc.nl/actueel/nieuws/2024/03/11/weinig-online-criminaliteit-zaken-leiden-tot-opsporing-vervolging-en-berechting-van-daders">said police needed to improve the training of officers</a> who handle criminal complaints so that they are more aware of the different types of online crime.</p><p>Many crimes were not investigated because victims were wrongly told that their case did not meet the threshold for filing a criminal complaint.</p><p>The report also recommended creating centralised teams to screen online crimes to improve the detection rate, and training detectives to remove their prejudices about the complexity of online crime.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tech/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232316</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 11:08:02 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Colon cancer cases down, survival rate up since screening began</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/colon-cancer-cases-down-survival-rate-up-since-screening-began/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232301 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-uncategorized newsletter-top-article"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Colon cancer cases down, survival rate up since screening began</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T09:51:18+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-232304" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_232304"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1125" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L-560x315.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L-1200x675.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L-768x432.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Depositphotos_271444342_L-1536x864.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-232304"> Mass screening has been linked to better survival chances. Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The chances of surviving colon cancer have improved since screenings were introduced for people aged 55 to 75 were introduced a decade ago, according to figures published by research centre IKNL.</p><p>Seven in 10 people who were diagnosed with colon cancer in 2017 were still alive five years later, compared to six in 10 who received a diagnosis in 2010. <a href="https://iknl.nl/nieuws/2024/trends-darmkanker-2024">Around 9,000 people a year in the Netherlands are found to have colon cancer</a>, down from a peak of 11,000 in 2015.</p><p>Before large-scale testing began around 20% of tumours found were at stage I, when the disease is still treatable. That proportion now stands at 30%.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The proportion of stage IV tumours, when the cancer has spread and is no longer operable, has fallen in the same period from 25% to 15%.</p><p>The number of tumours detected has also fallen since 2016 as more polyps have been removed before becoming cancerous. Rectal cancer cases have also fallen from 4,750 to just over 3,000 since 2014.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/uncategorized/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232301</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 09:51:18 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Giant Dutch ballot paper replaced by A3 format in trial</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/giant-dutch-ballot-paper-replaced-by-a3-format-in-trial/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232296 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-election category-dutch-european-news"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Giant Dutch ballot paper replaced by A3 format in trial</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T09:46:11+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-194064" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_194064"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="768" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM.jpeg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM.jpeg 1024w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM-560x420.jpeg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM-768x576.jpeg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM-640x480.jpeg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM-83x62.jpeg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/WhatsApp-Image-2022-03-16-at-1.31.47-PM-130x98.jpeg 130w" width="1024"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-194064"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Voters in five local council areas will test out new, smaller ballot papers in the European elections on June 6 – in an effort to reduce the current massive voting papers to a more manageable size.</p><p>The new A3 format will replace the one metre-wide ballot paper that voters have been struggling to unfold – and refold – in voting booths and which, despite their size, are not easy to read.</p><p>The papers are so big because they include both the name of every party in the election and every candidate. At the last general election in November, for example, 26 parties were listed on the ballot, each with up to 50 names.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The<a href="https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/verkiezingen/proef-met-nieuw-stembiljet"> trial</a>, conducted in Alphen aan den Rijn, Boekel, Borne, Midden-Delfland and Tynaarlo, will require voters to check two boxes, one for the party and one for a number representing the candidate.</p><p>The names of the candidates will be printed on a paper on the wall of the voting booth and are also in a booklet sent to voters.</p><p>Caretaker home affairs minister Hugo de Jonge said the new system would make voting “easier and more accessible” and that he didn’t expect the double tick would make the voting process too complicated.</p><p>If the trial is a success, the smaller ballot papers will be used at next local elections in 2026, De Jonge said.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/election/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/dutch-european-news/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232296</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 09:46:11 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Refugee centre breaks limit again, fine total reaches €60,000</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/refugee-centre-breaks-limit-again-fine-total-reaches-e60000/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232293 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-refugees category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Refugee centre breaks limit again, fine total reaches €60,000</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T09:06:52+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-110139" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_110139"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="683" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/refugees-COA-centre.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/refugees-COA-centre.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/refugees-COA-centre-560x382.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/refugees-COA-centre-768x525.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/refugees-COA-centre-300x205.jpg 300w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-110139"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The Ter Apel refugee reception centre in Groningen has now had too many refugees four times, which means the COA settlement agency has to pay €60,000 to the local authority in compensation.</p><p>Judges ruled earlier this year that COA would be liable for a €15,000 fine for every night the centre had more than 2,000 residents – the legal limit.</p><p>“We are doing all we can to meet our agreement with Westerwolde local authority and avoid fines,” the agency said. “But the high occupancy rate and stream of newcomers means this is not always possible.”</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><a href="https://www.rtvnoord.nl/nieuws/1138590/aanmeldcentrum-ter-apel-weer-te-vol-inmiddels-60000-euro-in-boetepot">RTV Noord</a> said at the weekend that the situation at Ter Apel is set to become more acute because a number of temporary refugee centres are due to close their doors in the coming weeks.</p><p>The broadcaster also said the COA is using tents in several locations close to Ter Apel where people have been moved at the last minute at night to avoid paying the fine.</p><p>In January, the senate voted in favour of new legislation which will spread the refugee more equitably around the country. Some councils have not provided any accommodation for asylum seekers, whether temporary or a permanent home for those who have been given residency permits.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/refugees/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232293</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 09:06:52 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Four party leaders retreat to country estate to break deadlock</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/four-party-leaders-retreat-to-country-estate-to-break-deadlock/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-232281 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-election-2023 category-politics newsletter-include"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Four party leaders retreat to country estate to break deadlock</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-03-11T08:47:42+00:00"> March 11, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-229160" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_229160"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1707" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-scaled.jpeg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-scaled.jpeg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-560x373.jpeg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-1200x800.jpeg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-360x240.jpeg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-768x512.jpeg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Wikipedia_Zwaluwenberg_achterkant-2048x1365.jpeg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-229160"> The talks will take place at the Zwaluwenberg Estate near Hilversum. Photo: Wikipedia</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Leaders of the four right-wing parties hoping to form a new Dutch government are to spend two days holding talks behind closed doors to try to decide what form the cabinet should take.</p><p>The four leaders – Geert Wilders of the PVV, Dilan Yesilgöz of the VVD, Pieter Omtzigt of NSC and Caroline van der Plas of the BBB – will meet at the Zwaluwenberg, a country estate on the edge of Hilversum, without their deputies.</p><p>The talks will be overseen by Kim Putters, chair of the social-economic council, whose findings will be presented to parliament and debated later this week.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>It is the first time the quartet have sat down together in four weeks, since Omtzigt withdrew from the first round of negotiations and said he would not join a coalition with the other three.</p><p>Putters had hoped to present his report to parliament at the start of this week, but last Thursday <a href="https://nos.nl/collectie/13962/liveblog/2511384-vier-partijleiders-met-putters-twee-dagen-op-landgoed-yesilgoz-hoopt-op-kabinet-voor-de-zomer">he said further discussions were needed</a> and he was now aiming to be finished by Wednesday. “We are on our way, but there is still a lot of ground to cover,” he said.</p><p>Speculation is growing in Dutch media that the parties will form a so-called “extra-parliamentary” cabinet, which includes ministers drawn from outside the political parties.</p><p>Omtzigt has said an extra-parliamentary administration is his preferred option, because it will be less bound by party discipline, which he argues will give MPs more scope to scrutinise ministerial proposals.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Yesilgöz has also expressed support for the extra-parliamentary option and says she is “hopeful” that a new government can be in place by the summer.</p><p>However, Wilders and Van der Plas still favour a conventional coalition of the four parties, which would have a majority in both houses of parliament.</p><p>An alternative coalition headed by the left-wing alliance GroenLinks-PvdA, led by former European commissioner Frans Timmermans, is not being seriously considered at this stage.</p><p>Both the VVD and NSC said after the election that they would prefer to support a minority government through a confidence and supply deal, rather than provide ministers as members of a coalition. The VVD is the only one of the four parties with a pool of experienced ministers to call on.</p><p> </p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/election-2023/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/politics/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=232281</guid><pubDate>Mon, 11 Mar 2024 08:47:42 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>